      • QUICK_RETURN_AFTER_CUTS_FOUND

        public final boolean QUICK_RETURN_AFTER_CUTS_FOUND
        The CutHandler invokes the AbstractCutGenerator(s) one by one to generate inequalities. When a particular cutGenerator does not yield any inequalities, the cutHandler will move on to the next registered cutGenerator. When quickReturnAfterCutsFound is set to true, the cutHandler will return as soon as any inequalities have been found. When set to false, all cutGenerators will be invoked. Default: true
